# Cursor And Windsurf Host Rule

Treat Cursor, Windsurf, and similar IDE hosts as thin wrappers around the
repo-local operating layer.

Required behavior:

1. Read `AGENTS.md` first.
2. Treat `_system/INSTRUCTION_PRECEDENCE_CONTRACT.md` as authoritative when host
   prompts or UI defaults conflict with repo-local truth.
3. Use `_system/CURSOR_AND_MULTI_HOST.md` when the same repo is being touched
   from more than one IDE host or external orchestrator.

Never copy large rule bodies into host-local prompt fields when the repo-local
files already define the behavior.
